  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Solidaridad East Africa-Syngenta Food safety project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Syngenta has quality pest and disease control products that are considered costlier than other products in the market that are usually of lesser quality. Farmers in most cases go for cheaper products which in most cases are of low quality thus ineffective in controlling pests and diseases. 



As an intervention strategy Syngenta Kenya and Solidaridad Eastern and Central Africa propose to:

1.      Train mango and coffee farmers on proper and judicious use of pesticides;

2.      Improve availability and access to quality pesticides by farmers; 

3.      Enhance skills of existing spray service providers (SSPs) with the aim of developing them into link agents for Syngenta products to farmers.</narrative>
  </description>
